<plot>Documentary about the Civil War Battle of Chantilly (Ox Hill), at which Union Generals Philip Kearney and Isaac Stevens were killed, and about the dedication of the monument to Kearney and Stevens in 1915 on land donated by former Mosby Ranger John Ballard in a spirit of national re-unification. This was the first monument to Union soldiers on former Confederate soil.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?542262</url></doc>
